The paper discusses a compiler for deep learning workloads, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on optimizing deep learning workloads. The second most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as deep learning is often used in computer vision applications. The third most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Augmented Reality), as deep learning is used in AR applications. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses optimizing deep learning workloads for diverse hardware back-ends.
